   1:Src/lm34.c    **** /**
   2:Src/lm34.c    ****  * lm34.c — LM34 temperature sensor via ADC1, channel 5 (PA0)
   3:Src/lm34.c    ****  *
   4:Src/lm34.c    ****  * ADC1 initialization sequence (RM0394 §18.4.6):
   5:Src/lm34.c    ****  *
   6:Src/lm34.c    ****  *   Step 1  — Exit deep power-down (DEEPPWD = 0)
   7:Src/lm34.c    ****  *   Step 2  — Enable internal voltage regulator (ADVREGEN = 1),
   8:Src/lm34.c    ****  *              wait ≥ 20 µs (t_ADCVREG_STUP per datasheet)
   9:Src/lm34.c    ****  *   Step 3  — Calibrate (ADCAL = 1 for single-ended), wait for ADCAL = 0
  10:Src/lm34.c    ****  *   Step 4  — Enable ADC (ADEN = 1), wait for ADRDY = 1
  11:Src/lm34.c    ****  *   Step 5  — Configure channel + sampling time
  12:Src/lm34.c    ****  *
  13:Src/lm34.c    ****  * ADC clock configuration:
  14:Src/lm34.c    ****  *   ADC1_COMMON->CCR  CKMODE[1:0] = 0b11  →  HCLK / 4 = 20 MHz
  15:Src/lm34.c    ****  *   (Synchronous mode; no async divider needed; BOOST = 0 for ≤ 20 MHz)
  16:Src/lm34.c    ****  *
  17:Src/lm34.c    ****  * Conversion formula — all integer, no floats:
  18:Src/lm34.c    ****  *
  19:Src/lm34.c    ****  *   T_F_tenths = raw × 3300 / 4095
  20:Src/lm34.c    ****  *
  21:Src/lm34.c    ****  * Why this works:
  22:Src/lm34.c    ****  *   LM34 sensitivity is 10 mV/°F → 1 mV = 0.1 °F = 1 tenth-°F.
  23:Src/lm34.c    ****  *   V_mV = raw × 3300 / 4095, and since 1 mV == 1 tenth-°F,
  24:Src/lm34.c    ****  *   T_F_tenths uses the exact same expression — convenient.
  25:Src/lm34.c    ****  */
  26:Src/lm34.c    **** 
  27:Src/lm34.c    **** #include "stm32l452xx.h"
  28:Src/lm34.c    **** #include "lm34.h"
  29:Src/lm34.c    **** #include "clock.h"
  30:Src/lm34.c    **** 
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Taylor\AppData\Local\Temp\ccepfqzb.s 			page 2


  31:Src/lm34.c    **** /* PA0 = ADC1 channel 5 */
  32:Src/lm34.c    **** #define LM34_ADC_CHANNEL   5U
  33:Src/lm34.c    **** 
